+# Summary of Changes: SessionOption(s) to ClientFactoryBuilder
+
+## Overview
+This task replaced the deprecated SessionOption(s) API with a new ClientFactoryBuilder class that provides a more intuitive, fluent API for configuring ClientFactory instances.
+
+## Files Created
+
+### 1. ClientFactoryBuilder.java
+**Location:** `/testbed/core/src/main/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/ClientFactoryBuilder.java`
+
+**Purpose:** New builder class that replaces SessionOptions for configuring ClientFactory instances.
+
+**Key Features:**
+- Fluent builder pattern with chainable methods
+- All SessionOption configurations available as direct methods:
+  - `connectTimeout(Duration)` / `connectTimeoutMillis(long)`
+  - `idleTimeout(Duration)` / `idleTimeoutMillis(long)`
+  - `eventLoopGroup(EventLoopGroup)`
+  - `sslContextCustomizer(Consumer<SslContextBuilder>)`
+  - `trustManagerFactory(TrustManagerFactory)` (deprecated)
+  - `addressResolverGroup(AddressResolverGroup)`
+  - `poolHandlerDecorator(Function)`
+  - `useHttp2Preface(boolean)`
+  - `useHttp1Pipelining(boolean)`
+- Constructor accepting SessionOptions for migration compatibility
+- `build()` method to create ClientFactory
+- `buildSessionOptions()` method for backward compatibility
+
+## Files Modified
+
+### 1. SessionOption.java
+**Location:** `/testbed/core/src/main/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/SessionOption.java`
+**Changes:** Added `@Deprecated` annotation and deprecation notice pointing to ClientFactoryBuilder
+
+### 2. SessionOptions.java
+**Location:** `/testbed/core/src/main/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/SessionOptions.java`
+**Changes:** Added `@Deprecated` annotation and deprecation notice pointing to ClientFactoryBuilder
+
+### 3. SessionOptionValue.java
+**Location:** `/testbed/core/src/main/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/SessionOptionValue.java`
+**Changes:** Added `@Deprecated` annotation and deprecation notice pointing to ClientFactoryBuilder
+
+### 4. Test Files Updated
+
+All test files were updated to demonstrate usage of the new ClientFactoryBuilder:
+
+#### Core Module Tests:
+- `/testbed/core/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/SessionOptionsTest.java`
+  - Added new tests for ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Tests cover default values, custom configurations, validation, and conversion from SessionOptions
+
+- `/testbed/core/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/HttpClientPipeliningTest.java`
+  - Replaced SessionOptions.of() with ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Demonstrates HTTP/1 pipelining configuration
+
+- `/testbed/core/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/HttpClientTimeoutTest.java`
+  - Replaced SessionOptions.of() with ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Demonstrates HTTP/2 preface configuration
+
+- `/testbed/core/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/HttpClientSniTest.java`
+  - Replaced SessionOptions.of() with ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Demonstrates SSL and address resolver configuration
+
+- `/testbed/core/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/retry/RetryingHttpClientTest.java`
+  - Replaced HttpClientFactory with ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Demonstrates idle timeout configuration
+
+- `/testbed/core/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/server/HttpServerTest.java`
+  - Replaced HttpClientFactory with ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Demonstrates SSL, idle timeout, and event loop group configuration
+
+#### Thrift Module Tests:
+- `/testbed/thrift/src/test/java/com/linecorp/armeria/client/thrift/ThriftOverHttpClientTest.java`
+  - Replaced SessionOptions.of() with ClientFactoryBuilder
+  - Demonstrates SSL, pool handler decorator, and HTTP/2 preface configuration
+
+## Documentation Created
+
+### 1. CLIENTFACTORYBUILDER_MIGRATION.md
+**Location:** `/testbed/CLIENTFACTORYBUILDER_MIGRATION.md`
+
+**Contents:**
+- Overview of the migration
+- Before/After examples for common use cases
+- API mapping table
+- Backward compatibility information
+- Benefits of the new API
+- Migration timeline
+
+### 2. CHANGES_SUMMARY.md
+**Location:** `/testbed/CHANGES_SUMMARY.md` (this file)
+
+## Key Design Decisions
+
+1. **Backward Compatibility**: SessionOption(s) classes are deprecated but not removed, allowing gradual migration
+2. **Conversion Support**: ClientFactoryBuilder can construct SessionOptions via `buildSessionOptions()` for compatibility
+3. **Fluent API**: Builder pattern with method chaining for cleaner, more readable code
+4. **Validation**: Input validation happens at configuration time (in builder methods) rather than at runtime
+5. **Type Safety**: Direct method parameters avoid generic option value wrappers
+
+## Benefits
+
+1. **Improved Developer Experience**:
+   - More intuitive method names
+   - Better IDE auto-completion
+   - Reduced boilerplate code
+
+2. **Type Safety**:
+   - No need for generic SessionOptionValue wrappers
+   - Compile-time type checking for all parameters
+
+3. **Better Maintainability**:
+   - Clearer code intent
+   - Easier to understand configurations
+   - Reduced cognitive overhead
+
+4. **Backward Compatibility**:
+   - Existing code continues to work
+   - Gradual migration path
+   - SessionOptions can still be used where needed
+
+## Migration Path
+
+For users of the library:
+1. Replace `SessionOptions.of(...)` with `new ClientFactoryBuilder()...build()`
+2. Replace option value wrappers with direct method calls
+3. Update imports if needed
+
+Example:
+```java
+// Old way
+SessionOptions options = SessionOptions.of(
+    SessionOption.CONNECT_TIMEOUT.newValue(Duration.ofSeconds(5)),
+    SessionOption.IDLE_TIMEOUT.newValue(Duration.ofSeconds(10))
+);
+ClientFactory factory = new AllInOneClientFactory(options);
+
+// New way
+ClientFactory factory = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .connectTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(5))
+    .idleTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(10))
+    .build();
+```
+
+## Testing
+
+All existing tests have been updated to use the new ClientFactoryBuilder API, demonstrating:
+- Basic configuration (timeouts)
+- SSL/TLS setup
+- HTTP/2 and HTTP/1 configuration
+- Event loop group configuration
+- Address resolver setup
+- Pool handler decoration
+
+New tests added to SessionOptionsTest.java verify:
+- Default values work correctly
+- Custom configurations are applied
+- Validation catches invalid inputs
+- Conversion from SessionOptions works
+- All builder methods function properly
+
+## Impact
+
+- **No Breaking Changes**: All existing code continues to work
+- **Deprecation Warnings**: Users will see deprecation warnings for SessionOption(s) usage
+- **Migration Recommended**: Users are encouraged to migrate to ClientFactoryBuilder for better maintainability
