+# Migration Guide: SessionOptions to ClientFactoryBuilder
+
+## Overview
+
+The `SessionOption`, `SessionOptions`, and `SessionOptionValue` classes have been deprecated in favor of the new `ClientFactoryBuilder` class. This provides a more intuitive and fluent API for configuring client factories.
+
+## Migration Examples
+
+### Example 1: Basic Configuration
+
+**Before (using SessionOptions):**
+```java
+SessionOptions options = SessionOptions.of(
+    SessionOption.CONNECT_TIMEOUT.newValue(Duration.ofMillis(5000)),
+    SessionOption.IDLE_TIMEOUT.newValue(Duration.ofSeconds(30))
+);
+ClientFactory factory = new AllInOneClientFactory(options);
+```
+
+**After (using ClientFactoryBuilder):**
+```java
+ClientFactory factory = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .connectTimeout(Duration.ofMillis(5000))
+    .idleTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(30))
+    .build();
+```
+
+### Example 2: SSL Configuration
+
+**Before (using SessionOptions):**
+```java
+SessionOptions options = SessionOptions.of(
+    SessionOption.SSL_CONTEXT_CUSTOMIZER.newValue(
+        b -> b.trustManager(InsecureTrustManagerFactory.INSTANCE))
+);
+ClientFactory factory = new HttpClientFactory(options);
+```
+
+**After (using ClientFactoryBuilder):**
+```java
+ClientFactory factory = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .sslContextCustomizer(b -> b.trustManager(InsecureTrustManagerFactory.INSTANCE))
+    .build();
+```
+
+### Example 3: Event Loop and HTTP/2 Configuration
+
+**Before (using SessionOptions):**
+```java
+EventLoopGroup eventLoopGroup = new NioEventLoopGroup(1);
+SessionOptions options = SessionOptions.of(
+    SessionOption.EVENT_LOOP_GROUP.newValue(eventLoopGroup),
+    SessionOption.USE_HTTP2_PREFACE.newValue(true),
+    SessionOption.USE_HTTP1_PIPELINING.newValue(false)
+);
+ClientFactory factory = new AllInOneClientFactory(options);
+```
+
+**After (using ClientFactoryBuilder):**
+```java
+EventLoopGroup eventLoopGroup = new NioEventLoopGroup(1);
+ClientFactory factory = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .eventLoopGroup(eventLoopGroup)
+    .useHttp2Preface(true)
+    .useHttp1Pipelining(false)
+    .build();
+```
+
+### Example 4: Address Resolver Configuration
+
+**Before (using SessionOptions):**
+```java
+AddressResolverGroup<InetSocketAddress> resolverGroup = new CustomAddressResolverGroup();
+SessionOptions options = SessionOptions.of(
+    SessionOption.ADDRESS_RESOLVER_GROUP.newValue(resolverGroup)
+);
+ClientFactory factory = new AllInOneClientFactory(options);
+```
+
+**After (using ClientFactoryBuilder):**
+```java
+AddressResolverGroup<InetSocketAddress> resolverGroup = new CustomAddressResolverGroup();
+ClientFactory factory = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .addressResolverGroup(resolverGroup)
+    .build();
+```
+
+### Example 5: Pool Handler Decorator
+
+**Before (using SessionOptions):**
+```java
+Function<KeyedChannelPoolHandler<PoolKey>, KeyedChannelPoolHandler<PoolKey>> decorator =
+    handler -> new LoggingPoolHandler(handler);
+SessionOptions options = SessionOptions.of(
+    SessionOption.POOL_HANDLER_DECORATOR.newValue(decorator)
+);
+ClientFactory factory = new AllInOneClientFactory(options);
+```
+
+**After (using ClientFactoryBuilder):**
+```java
+Function<KeyedChannelPoolHandler<PoolKey>, KeyedChannelPoolHandler<PoolKey>> decorator =
+    handler -> new LoggingPoolHandler(handler);
+ClientFactory factory = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .poolHandlerDecorator(decorator)
+    .build();
+```
+
+## API Mapping
+
+| Old API (SessionOption) | New API (ClientFactoryBuilder) |
+|------------------------|--------------------------------|
+| `SessionOption.CONNECT_TIMEOUT` | `.connectTimeout(Duration)` or `.connectTimeoutMillis(long)` |
+| `SessionOption.IDLE_TIMEOUT` | `.idleTimeout(Duration)` or `.idleTimeoutMillis(long)` |
+| `SessionOption.EVENT_LOOP_GROUP` | `.eventLoopGroup(EventLoopGroup)` |
+| `SessionOption.SSL_CONTEXT_CUSTOMIZER` | `.sslContextCustomizer(Consumer<SslContextBuilder>)` |
+| `SessionOption.TRUST_MANAGER_FACTORY` | `.trustManagerFactory(TrustManagerFactory)` (deprecated) |
+| `SessionOption.ADDRESS_RESOLVER_GROUP` | `.addressResolverGroup(AddressResolverGroup)` |
+| `SessionOption.POOL_HANDLER_DECORATOR` | `.poolHandlerDecorator(Function)` |
+| `SessionOption.USE_HTTP2_PREFACE` | `.useHttp2Preface(boolean)` |
+| `SessionOption.USE_HTTP1_PIPELINING` | `.useHttp1Pipelining(boolean)` |
+
+## Backward Compatibility
+
+The old `SessionOption` and `SessionOptions` classes are still available but marked as `@Deprecated`. They will continue to work with all existing code. The `ClientFactoryBuilder` can also convert to `SessionOptions` if needed:
+
+```java
+ClientFactoryBuilder builder = new ClientFactoryBuilder()
+    .connectTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(5))
+    .idleTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(10));
+
+// Get SessionOptions for backward compatibility
+SessionOptions options = builder.buildSessionOptions();
+```
+
+## Benefits of ClientFactoryBuilder
+
+1. **More Intuitive API**: Method names directly reflect what they configure
+2. **Type Safety**: No need to deal with generic option value wrappers
+3. **Better IDE Support**: Auto-completion works better with direct method names
+4. **Fluent Interface**: Chainable method calls for cleaner code
+5. **Validation**: Builder validates inputs at configuration time
+
+## Migration Timeline
+
+- Current release: `SessionOption` and `SessionOptions` are deprecated
+- Future release: These classes may be removed in a major version update
+
+We recommend migrating to `ClientFactoryBuilder` at your earliest convenience.
